==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Devastate
<hw>Dev"as*tate</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Devastated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Devastating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>devastatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>devastare</ets> to devastate;
<ets>de</ets> + <ets>vastare</ets> to lay waste, <ets>vastus</ets>
waste. See <er>Vast</er>.]</ety> <def>To lay waste; to ravage; to
desolate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whole countries . . . were <qex>devastated</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To waste; ravage; desolate; destroy; demolish;
plunder; pillage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>devastated</ent>⟦br⟧
